  "chapter": {
    "number": 3,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Jesus Our Apostle and High Priest"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Therefore, holy brothers, who share in the heavenly calling, set your focus on Jesus, the apostle and high priest whom we confess."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "He was faithful to the One who appointed Him, just as Moses was faithful in all God’s house.",
          {
            "noteId": 2377
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "For Jesus has been counted worthy of greater glory than Moses, just as the builder of a house has greater honor than the house itself."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "And every house is built by someone, but God is the builder of everything."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          "Now Moses was faithful as a servant in all God’s house,",
          {
            "noteId": 2378
          },
          "testifying to what would be spoken later."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          "But Christ is faithful as the Son over God’s house. And we are His house, if we hold firmly",
          {
            "noteId": 2379
          },
          "to our confidence and the hope of which we boast."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Do Not Harden Your Hearts"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          "Therefore, as the Holy Spirit says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Today, if you hear His voice,",
            "poem": 1
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "do not harden your hearts,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "as you did in the rebellion,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in the day of testing in the wilderness,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "where your fathers tested and tried Me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and for forty years saw My works.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore I was angry with that generation,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I said,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "‘Their hearts are always going astray,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and they have not known My ways.’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So I swore on oath in My anger,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘They shall never enter My rest.’”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2380
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Peril of Unbelief"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          "See to it, brothers, that none of you has a wicked heart of unbelief that turns away from the living God."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          "But exhort one another daily, as long as it is called today, so that none of you may be hardened by sin’s deceitfulness."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          "We have come to share in Christ if we hold firmly to the end the assurance we had at first."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          "As it has been said:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Today, if you hear His voice,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "do not harden your hearts,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "as you did in the rebellion.”",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2381
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          "For who were the ones who heard and rebelled? Were they not all those Moses led out of Egypt?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          "And with whom was God angry for forty years? Was it not with those who sinned, whose bodies fell in the wilderness?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          "And to whom did He swear that they would never enter His rest? Was it not to those who disobeyed?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          "So we see that it was because of their unbelief that they were unable to enter."
        ]
      }
    ],
